article.headline: Winthrop 90, Radford 75
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- James Shuler scored 23 and was 6-of-6 from the free-throw line in the final minute to hold off Radford for a 90-75 victory Saturday night. Radford (8-7, 1-2 Big South Conference) came to within 80-73 with 1:54 left before sending Shuler to the line. Shuler finished 8-of-8 from the line and led five Winthrop players in double digits. Craig Bradshaw had a career-high 20 for the Eagles (9-4, 3-0). Torrell Martin had 15 points, Chris Gaynor added 13 and Phillip Williams had 10. Whit Holcomb-Faye had a career-high 37 points for Radford including shooting 16-of-16 from the free-throw line. Chris Oliver added 14 -- all in the first half -- and Reggie McIntyre had 12. Radford had 20 of its 25 fouls in the second half, sending the Eagles to the line 29 times for 19 points. Winthrop also had foul trouble in the half, amassing 13 of its 19 fouls. Radford shot 95.8 percent from the charity stripe on 23-of-24 shooting. Winthrop outscored Radford 30-6 in the paint and outrebounded the Highlanders 40-31. Winthrop led 50-37 at halftime, and both teams shot 32.1 percent in the second half. Winthrop didn't have a field goal the final 5:23 of the game. Winthrop won its 18th consecutive regular season Big South game.
